This paper involves the use of computational methods for the analysis and interpretation of protein expression in immunohistochemistry (IHC) images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the study explores the use of crowdsourcing as an alternative approach for the quantification of IHC images, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning algorithms for automated scoring of IHC images, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) and deep learning (cs.DL) sub-categories.
